this is all questions and answers:

1.#Write a python script to take your name as input from the user and then print it.
user_input = input("enter name here")
print(user_input)

2.#Write a python script to take input from the user. Input must be a number
user_input = int(input("enter only number here"))
print(user_input)

3.#Write a python script which takes two numbers from the user, then calculate their sum and display the result.
user_input1 = int(input("enter first number here"))
user_input2 = int(input("enter second number here"))
c = user_input1 + user_input2
print(c)

4.#Write a python script which takes the radius from the user and display area of a circle.
user_input = int(input("enter radius here"))
c = 2*3.14*user_input
print("area of a circle is ",c)

5.#Write a python script to calculate the square of a number. Number is entered by the user.
user_input = int(input("enter number here"))
squr = user_input**2
print("square of ",user_input ,"is ",squr)

6.#Write a python script to calculate the area of Triangle. Number is entered by the user
base = int(input("enter triabgle base here"))
height = int(input("enter triabgle height here"))
formula = (base*height)/2
print(formula)

7.#Write a python script to calculate average of three numbers, entered by the user
user_input1 = int(input("enter three number to get average and first number is "))
user_input2 = int(input("enter second number is"))
user_input3 = int(input("enter three number is"))
avg = (user_input1 + user_input2 + user_input3)/3
print(avg)

8.#Write a python script to calculate simple interest
borrow_money = int(input("enter money you borrow"))
rate = int(input("enter rate here"))
year = int(input("enter how many year to return borrow money"))
simple_interest = borrow_money +(borrow_money*rate*year)/100
print(simple_interest)

9.# Write a python script to calculate the volume of a cuboid.
lenght = int(input("enter lenght   here"))
height = int(input("enter t height here"))
width = int(input("enter width height here"))
formula = lenght*width*height
print("the volume of a cuboid is ",formula)

10.#Write a python script to calculate area of a rectangle
lenght = int(input("enter t lenght here"))
width = int(input("enter width height here"))
formula = lenght*width
print("the area of a rectangle is ",formula)



